article.headline: Central Michigan 87, Morehead State 76
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Chris Kellerman scored a career-high 25 points and Central Michigan broke a seven-game losing streak as the Chippewas beat Morehead State 87-76 on Saturday. After trailing early in the first half, Central Michigan (4-19) went on a 12-0 run that featured and alley-oop dunk from Sefton Barrett for a 22-15 lead. The Chippewas pushed their lead to 22 points in the second half on the strength of a 15-2 run, including seven points from Barrett. The Eagles (4-21) responded with a run of their own and cut the lead to 71-68 with 3:44 to play on a putback by Ryan Allen. A 3-pointer by Kellerman pushed Central Michigan's lead back to six points, and the Eagles would get no closer than four points the rest of the way as the Chippewas hit 11-of-16 free throws down the stretch. Barrett and Giordan Watson each scored 14 points for the Chippewas, while Aaron Richie added 14 off the bench and Eddie Spencer scored 10. Tyke Cockerham led the Eagles with 21 points, Smith scored 17, and Shaun Williams had 14 points and 10 rebounds. Ryan Allen also scored 14.
